WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-US

00:00:02.600 --> 00:00:04.733
In order to explain the whitening issue thoroughly,

00:00:04.733 --> 00:00:06.866
I recently

00:00:06.866 --> 00:00:09.900
updated the details of the 16-type whitening method in two parts.

00:00:09.900 --> 00:00:13.100
As a result, I received many questions about whitening,

00:00:13.100 --> 00:00:14.600
so today is a straightforward

00:00:14.600 --> 00:00:17.100
whitening Q&amp;A.

00:00:17.100 --> 00:00:18.700
I hope the answers to these questions

00:00:18.700 --> 00:00:20.533
can help more people. Let me

00:00:27.333 --> 00:00:29.866
first answer the most frequently asked question

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:32.866
, which is, aren't there 4 types of darkening? Is

00:00:32.866 --> 00:00:34.600
it possible for a person

00:00:34.600 --> 00:00:37.400
to have two types at the same time?

00:00:37.400 --> 00:00:40.700
What if I have all four types ?

00:00:40.900 --> 00:00:43.066
First of all, the answer is

00:00:43.066 --> 00:00:46.433
that it is possible for our face to have multiple types at the same time

00:00:46.500 --> 00:00:48.733
. What should we do in this case?

00:00:48.733 --> 00:00:50.933
Never solve them all at once

00:00:50.933 --> 00:00:52.666
, but solve them one by one.

00:00:52.733 --> 00:00:55.700
Why can't all problems be solved at the same time?

00:00:55.700 --> 00:00:57.433
Because each of

00:00:57.433 --> 00:01:00.233
our whitening ingredients is irritating.

00:01:00.333 --> 00:01:01.900
The more you stack them, the more

00:01:01.900 --> 00:01:03.500
irritating it will be. The bigger

00:01:03.500 --> 00:01:05.433
it is, the more likely it is that instead of whitening

00:01:05.433 --> 00:01:07.066
, you may also get allergic reactions.

00:01:07.066 --> 00:01:07.866
So

00:01:07.866 --> 00:01:10.500
we can't

00:01:10.500 --> 00:01:11.666
apply all these types of products on our face at once

00:01:11.666 --> 00:01:13.833
, but we have to solve

00:01:13.866 --> 00:01:15.800
them one by one. When solving them one by one,

00:01:15.800 --> 00:01:18.200
in what order should we solve them?

00:01:18.266 --> 00:01:19.800
Start with the easier ones with

00:01:19.800 --> 00:01:20.600
a short cycle

00:01:20.600 --> 00:01:22.200
and quick results

00:01:22.200 --> 00:01:24.133
, and then solve the more difficult ones

00:01:24.133 --> 00:01:25.800
with a longer cycle.

00:01:25.800 --> 00:01:27.800
If they are arranged in order,

00:01:27.800 --> 00:01:32.000
it is tanning type → red and black type → dull type → yellow type.

00:01:32.066 --> 00:01:33.666
What specific products should be used?

00:01:33.666 --> 00:01:34.200
Friends

00:01:34.200 --> 00:01:37.700
can look back at

00:01:37.700 --> 00:01:39.600
the relevant product introductions in

00:01:40.400 --> 00:01:41.433
the second half of the 16-type whitening method.

00:01:41.433 --> 00:01:42.833
The next question is

00:01:42.833 --> 00:01:44.066
how to remove liver spots

00:01:44.233 --> 00:01:46.866
? First of all, we have to talk about the term liver spots. It

00:01:46.866 --> 00:01:49.300
is actually a more popular name. It is

00:01:49.300 --> 00:01:51.033
the symptoms caused by liver qi stagnation

00:01:51.033 --> 00:01:54.700
in traditional Chinese medicine , not that it is really related to the liver.

00:01:54.700 --> 00:01:57.000
This type of spot is scientifically called chloasma.

00:01:57.000 --> 00:01:57.700
Chloasma

00:01:57.700 --> 00:02:01.300
is generally

00:02:01.300 --> 00:02:02.233
related

00:02:02.233 --> 00:02:03.900
to our endocrine system

00:02:03.900 --> 00:02:05.900
, including changes in hormones.

00:02:05.900 --> 00:02:08.933
Therefore, many female friends will develop chloasma before and after childbirth

00:02:08.933 --> 00:02:12.200
or when entering menopause.

00:02:12.233 --> 00:02:14.400
What should I do if it already has chloasma

00:02:14.433 --> 00:02:16.066
? First of all, it should be pointed out that

00:02:16.066 --> 00:02:19.066
cosmetics cannot remove spots,

00:02:19.100 --> 00:02:20.333
they can only lighten them

00:02:20.433 --> 00:02:21.733
because many chloasma

00:02:21.733 --> 00:02:24.100
grow in deeper parts of the skin,

00:02:24.100 --> 00:02:26.833
such as the dermis or the deeper epidermis.

00:02:26.833 --> 00:02:28.866
When we use our cosmetics,

00:02:28.866 --> 00:02:31.533
because the skin barrier is a complete system

00:02:31.533 --> 00:02:34.400
, the deeper the product is absorbed,

00:02:34.400 --> 00:02:36.233
the

00:02:36.300 --> 00:02:39.033
lower its concentration will be. When it is absorbed near your spots,

00:02:39.033 --> 00:02:39.866
its concentration

00:02:39.866 --> 00:02:42.466
is far from reaching the effective concentration.

00:02:42.466 --> 00:02:43.500
Then someone may ask,

00:02:43.500 --> 00:02:45.233
can't I just increase the concentration

00:02:45.233 --> 00:02:47.100
and use a higher one?

00:02:47.100 --> 00:02:48.600
But it doesn't work

00:02:48.633 --> 00:02:50.233
because Because when the concentration is very high,

00:02:50.233 --> 00:02:51.700
the safety of using it on your epidermis

00:02:51.700 --> 00:02:54.233
cannot be guaranteed.

00:02:54.233 --> 00:02:55.300
It will irritate you and

00:02:55.300 --> 00:02:56.133
you will be allergic

00:02:56.133 --> 00:02:58.133
, and you will not achieve the effect you want.

00:02:58.433 --> 00:03:01.466
So what if you really want to remove spots?

00:03:01.466 --> 00:03:02.266
I suggest

00:03:02.266 --> 00:03:04.100
that you consult a dermatologist

00:03:04.100 --> 00:03:05.700
or a cosmetologist in the hospital

00:03:05.700 --> 00:03:08.500
to see if there are any related medical beauty projects

00:03:08.500 --> 00:03:10.533
that can help you remove the spots.

00:03:10.600 --> 00:03:11.666
Common projects

00:03:11.666 --> 00:03:13.233
are such as fractional laser

00:03:13.233 --> 00:03:15.266
ultra-picosecond, photorejuvenation, etc.

00:03:15.333 --> 00:03:17.266
So which specific project to choose?

00:03:17.266 --> 00:03:19.066
We must go to a regular hospital

00:03:19.066 --> 00:03:21.300
and find a regular doctor to give you advice.

00:03:21.600 --> 00:03:23.700
Another very important point is that

00:03:23.700 --> 00:03:26.533
after we have completed these freckle removal projects,

00:03:26.533 --> 00:03:30.533
we must also pay attention to preventing darkening and recurring spots.

00:03:30.600 --> 00:03:32.133
There are two key actions

00:03:32.133 --> 00:03:33.700
for this preventive measure.

00:03:33.700 --> 00:03:35.666
The first is sun protection

00:03:35.666 --> 00:03:38.900
because sun protection can prevent you from getting spots

00:03:38.900 --> 00:03:40.400
by eliminating the stimulation of ultraviolet rays.

00:03:40.400 --> 00:03:41.133
And even if the spot has already grown,

00:03:41.133 --> 00:03:44.033
sunscreen

00:03:44.033 --> 00:03:47.500
can help you prevent the spot from growing too deep

00:03:47.500 --> 00:03:48.733
or growing more.

00:03:48.800 --> 00:03:49.933
The second action

00:03:49.933 --> 00:03:52.466
is that we can actively repair the barrier

00:03:52.466 --> 00:03:54.500
and choose mild whitening products.

00:03:54.500 --> 00:03:55.466
For related products,

00:03:55.466 --> 00:03:56.533
we can refer to

00:03:56.533 --> 00:03:58.633
red-black and yellow-gas products,

00:03:58.633 --> 00:04:00.933
such as VC derivatives containing tranexamic acid

00:04:00.933 --> 00:04:02.033
or arbutin

00:04:02.033 --> 00:04:04.300
and other types of mild whitening products.

00:04:04.666 --> 00:04:06.133
Let’s talk

00:04:06.133 --> 00:04:07.600
about the third question.

00:04:07.600 --> 00:04:11.400
Several friends asked: Why is my skin very white

00:04:11.400 --> 00:04:12.933
after washing my face or applying a mask,

00:04:13.066 --> 00:04:16.500
but it becomes dull and dark again after a while?

00:04:16.533 --> 00:04:19.066
In this case, do I need whitening?

00:04:19.100 --> 00:04:20.100
This phenomenon occurs

00:04:20.100 --> 00:04:21.466
to many people

00:04:21.466 --> 00:04:23.633
, but it can be divided into two situations.

00:04:23.733 --> 00:04:26.800
The first situation is that you have oily skin

00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:29.033
. When you just wash your face,

00:04:29.033 --> 00:04:31.000
your skin is The oil on your skin is washed off,

00:04:31.000 --> 00:04:31.600
so

00:04:31.600 --> 00:04:34.233
the original color of your skin is revealed

00:04:34.233 --> 00:04:35.433
, which is very white.

00:04:35.466 --> 00:04:37.133
But as time goes by,

00:04:37.133 --> 00:04:38.500
you produce oil again,

00:04:38.500 --> 00:04:40.600
and this oil will oxidize.

00:04:40.600 --> 00:04:43.433
After oxidation, this oil will become yellow

00:04:43.433 --> 00:04:44.933
or even soy sauce-colored,

00:04:44.933 --> 00:04:46.733
and you will feel that you have become darker

00:04:46.733 --> 00:04:49.433
and darker. People in this situation

00:04:49.433 --> 00:04:52.433
need to use products that can control oil

00:04:52.433 --> 00:04:55.333
while resisting the oxidation of your oil.

00:04:55.333 --> 00:04:57.633
Typical

00:04:57.633 --> 00:05:00.500
products of this type

00:05:00.500 --> 00:05:04.066
include

00:05:04.066 --> 00:05:05.866
essences containing trioxyethyl ascorbic acid, a water- and oil-soluble VC.

00:05:05.866 --> 00:05:07.400
For example, Kiehl's Whitening Bottle

00:05:07.400 --> 00:05:10.233
can resist the oxidation of your oil, so that

00:05:10.233 --> 00:05:12.600
your whiteness can last longer.

00:05:12.666 --> 00:05:13.333
In the final analysis,

00:05:13.333 --> 00:05:15.100
this is not a skin color problem

00:05:15.100 --> 00:05:18.200
, but a problem of the oxidation of your oil.

00:05:18.500 --> 00:05:19.600
Second, The first situation

00:05:19.600 --> 00:05:21.633
is that you have dry skin.

00:05:21.633 --> 00:05:24.233
After washing your face and applying a facial mask,

00:05:24.233 --> 00:05:25.000
because you have been in contact with a lot of water

00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:26.933
in a short period of time

00:05:26.933 --> 00:05:29.266
, the hydration level of your skin

00:05:29.300 --> 00:05:31.033
will increase significantly

00:05:31.033 --> 00:05:34.700
. The skin will appear more transparent, and

00:05:34.700 --> 00:05:36.300
you will look brighter

00:05:36.300 --> 00:05:37.266
and whiter.

00:05:37.433 --> 00:05:38.633
What does this mean?

00:05:38.633 --> 00:05:42.600
This means that under normal circumstances, you are actually dark,

00:05:42.800 --> 00:05:46.000
and you can only become white under special circumstances.

00:05:46.000 --> 00:05:47.900
This whiteness is an illusion,

00:05:47.900 --> 00:05:49.033
not real whiteness . Most of

00:05:49.266 --> 00:05:51.266
the friends who raise such questions

00:05:51.266 --> 00:05:54.900
belong to the yellow type among the four types of darkening.

00:05:55.133 --> 00:05:57.133
Because the first three types are difficult

00:05:57.133 --> 00:05:58.133
to make you

00:05:58.133 --> 00:06:00.333
look much whiter by washing your face and applying a facial mask,

00:06:00.400 --> 00:06:03.400
then when choosing products, we should choose the yellow type

00:06:03.400 --> 00:06:06.933
and then the corresponding products for dry skin.

00:06:06.966 --> 00:06:07.600
Having said that,

00:06:07.600 --> 00:06:08.833
I have another suggestion. Everyone says

00:06:08.833 --> 00:06:09.866
that although applying a facial mask

00:06:09.866 --> 00:06:13.333
can quickly make your skin look clear

00:06:13.433 --> 00:06:14.633
, I recommend

00:06:14.633 --> 00:06:17.333
not using it more than three times a week.

00:06:17.333 --> 00:06:19.900
Repeatedly and frequently increasing skin hydration

00:06:19.900 --> 00:06:21.266
will have a side effect

00:06:21.266 --> 00:06:24.133
: it will weaken your skin barrier, allowing

00:06:24.200 --> 00:06:26.833
external stimuli to penetrate more easily,

00:06:26.833 --> 00:06:28.633
making your skin more sensitive.

00:06:29.100 --> 00:06:30.200
The fourth question

00:06:30.200 --> 00:06:32.466
is, after being exposed to the sun, I didn't get a tan,

00:06:32.466 --> 00:06:33.833
but I got spots.

00:06:33.833 --> 00:06:36.300
Which of the four types of darkening does it belong to?

00:06:36.400 --> 00:06:38.733
The answer is red-black type

00:06:38.833 --> 00:06:41.200
because its physiological chain is actually like this:

00:06:41.200 --> 00:06:43.333
when you are stimulated by ultraviolet rays,

00:06:43.333 --> 00:06:45.900
your skin cells will produce

00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:48.633
inflammation, which stimulates the production of melanin.

00:06:48.700 --> 00:06:49.500
The key to

00:06:49.500 --> 00:06:50.266
the red-black type

00:06:50.266 --> 00:06:53.333
is also the melanin production triggered by inflammation,

00:06:53.400 --> 00:06:55.600
so this type belongs to the red-black type

00:06:55.733 --> 00:06:56.700
related products.

00:06:56.700 --> 00:06:59.600
We can refer to the related

00:06:59.600 --> 00:07:01.533
products containing tranexamic acid

00:07:01.533 --> 00:07:02.600
in the red and black types. The next question is,

00:07:02.866 --> 00:07:06.433
is tranexamic acid poorly absorbed?

00:07:06.600 --> 00:07:07.933
The answer is yes.

00:07:08.100 --> 00:07:09.600
The ingredients of our cosmetics

00:07:09.600 --> 00:07:12.466
have four chemical properties: hydrophilic

00:07:12.466 --> 00:07:14.400
, lipophilic, amphiphilic

00:07:14.400 --> 00:07:16.433
, and amphiphobic .

00:07:16.500 --> 00:07:19.700
Among them, the more lipophilic, the better the absorption.

00:07:19.700 --> 00:07:20.600
Why?

00:07:20.600 --> 00:07:23.066
Because the cell membrane of our skin cells

00:07:23.066 --> 00:07:26.533
is composed of a phospholipid bilayer.

00:07:26.533 --> 00:07:27.433
This phospholipid

00:07:27.433 --> 00:07:28.466
is a kind of oil.

00:07:28.466 --> 00:07:30.900
So if the ingredient is more lipophilic,

00:07:30.900 --> 00:07:34.233
the better its affinity with the phospholipid bilayer, the

00:07:34.233 --> 00:07:35.700
easier and faster

00:07:35.700 --> 00:07:37.066
it will be absorbed

00:07:37.066 --> 00:07:38.133
. Tranexamic acid

00:07:38.133 --> 00:07:39.200
is not lipophilic, it is hydrophilic,

00:07:39.200 --> 00:07:40.266
so it

00:07:40.266 --> 00:07:42.900
has a natural repulsion effect

00:07:42.900 --> 00:07:44.833
with the cell membrane of the skin,

00:07:44.833 --> 00:07:46.900
and its absorption is not

00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:49.100
good . But in fact, we don’t need to worry too much

00:07:49.100 --> 00:07:50.433
because the people who make the formulas,

00:07:50.433 --> 00:07:51.733
these cosmetic brands,

00:07:51.733 --> 00:07:53.933
are more worried about this issue than users

00:07:53.933 --> 00:07:54.266
. So

00:07:54.266 --> 00:07:57.200
they will take many measures to solve this problem

00:07:57.200 --> 00:07:59.433
, such as encapsulating tranexamic acid and

00:07:59.433 --> 00:08:00.533
liposomalizing

00:08:00.533 --> 00:08:03.866
it or making the formula into nanoemulsion, etc.

00:08:03.866 --> 00:08:07.233
They will promote the absorption of tranexamic acid.

00:08:07.233 --> 00:08:10.100
For example, Shiseido's patented ingredient m-tranexamic acid

00:08:10.100 --> 00:08:12.000
is used to encapsulate tranexamic acid.

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:12.600
In addition,

00:08:12.600 --> 00:08:15.466
many products will be combined with niacinamide or polyols

00:08:15.466 --> 00:08:18.100
or acids to promote the absorption of tranexamic acid.

00:08:18.233 --> 00:08:21.433
So as long as it is a product produced by a regular brand,

00:08:21.600 --> 00:08:23.066
we can just use it.

00:08:23.300 --> 00:08:26.133
The next question is that microneedles will also irritate the skin

00:08:26.133 --> 00:08:28.133
, so why does the skin become better

00:08:28.133 --> 00:08:30.033
after microneedling ?

00:08:30.300 --> 00:08:31.333
The friend who asked this question

00:08:31.333 --> 00:08:32.833
may be confused

00:08:32.833 --> 00:08:34.066
because I said before that

00:08:34.066 --> 00:08:37.500
all types of darkening come from stimulation,

00:08:37.633 --> 00:08:39.666
so microneedles are also irritating, so why

00:08:39.666 --> 00:08:40.933
does the skin become better

00:08:40.933 --> 00:08:42.866
after using it ?

00:08:43.000 --> 00:08:45.066
The key to this question is that

00:08:45.066 --> 00:08:48.033
the stimulation I mentioned

00:08:48.033 --> 00:08:50.833
is completely different from the stimulation of microneedles. There are two types of stimulation.

00:08:50.833 --> 00:08:52.100
The stimulation I'm talking about is,

00:08:52.100 --> 00:08:53.500
for example, the stimulation of ultraviolet rays and

00:08:53.500 --> 00:08:54.400
the stimulation of endocrine changes.

00:08:54.400 --> 00:08:57.133
It's very complex,

00:08:57.133 --> 00:08:58.333
with a chain reaction

00:08:58.333 --> 00:08:59.200
, chemical and

00:08:59.200 --> 00:09:00.100
physiological.

00:09:00.100 --> 00:09:01.700
The stimulation of microneedles

00:09:01.700 --> 00:09:03.066
is physical

00:09:03.066 --> 00:09:04.200
and single.

00:09:04.400 --> 00:09:05.100
For example,

00:09:05.100 --> 00:09:08.066
if your skin is your house,

00:09:08.100 --> 00:09:09.700
then the stimulation I'm talking about

00:09:09.700 --> 00:09:12.400
is like a thief breaking into your house.

00:09:12.433 --> 00:09:13.133
The thief

00:09:13.133 --> 00:09:14.266
may steal things

00:09:14.266 --> 00:09:15.433
or smash and rob, and

00:09:15.433 --> 00:09:16.233
you don't know

00:09:16.233 --> 00:09:18.000
what's going on, so you can only

00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:19.033
fight him fiercely.

00:09:19.100 --> 00:09:20.466
In the process,

00:09:20.466 --> 00:09:22.266
your house is a mess.

00:09:22.300 --> 00:09:23.733
The stimulation of microneedles

00:09:23.733 --> 00:09:25.833
is like a stone flying from outside your house

00:09:25.833 --> 00:09:27.666
and breaking your window.

00:09:27.666 --> 00:09:28.900
You repair the window and

00:09:28.900 --> 00:09:31.133
your house is intact.

00:09:31.133 --> 00:09:34.633
So why does the skin get better after using microneedles?

00:09:34.666 --> 00:09:36.700
The microneedles we usually use

00:09:36.700 --> 00:09:41.500
are usually extremely small needles

00:09:41.500 --> 00:09:43.866
between 0.25 mm and 2.5 mm.

00:09:43.866 --> 00:09:47.633
They pass through By creating micro-wounds on your skin

00:09:47.633 --> 00:09:51.600
to promote the production of local collagen and EGF,

00:09:51.633 --> 00:09:53.933
your micro-wounds can be repaired.

00:09:53.933 --> 00:09:55.100
During the repair process,

00:09:55.100 --> 00:09:57.533
your old acne scars and

00:09:57.533 --> 00:10:00.133
marks will heal and

00:10:00.133 --> 00:10:01.300
grow again.

00:10:01.400 --> 00:10:03.100
So after the micro-needle treatment,

00:10:03.100 --> 00:10:05.433
you will feel that your skin is better than before.

00:10:05.433 --> 00:10:07.733
But there is one thing you need to pay special attention to

00:10:07.733 --> 00:10:08.900
. Sometimes micro-needles

00:10:08.900 --> 00:10:12.300
are used

00:10:12.300 --> 00:10:13.266
to make other products absorb better.

00:10:13.533 --> 00:10:16.000
Think about it, if you make a lot of holes in your skin,

00:10:16.000 --> 00:10:17.700
then no matter what product you use later

00:10:17.700 --> 00:10:19.433
, it will absorb more,

00:10:19.433 --> 00:10:22.600
right? If this product is irritating,

00:10:22.600 --> 00:10:25.333
then the irritation will be amplified several times.

00:10:25.500 --> 00:10:27.066
So there is a risk

00:10:27.066 --> 00:10:27.733
in

00:10:27.733 --> 00:10:30.333
what product you use later.

00:10:30.333 --> 00:10:31.133
I would like to remind everyone

00:10:31.133 --> 00:10:32.866
of this point. I hope everyone will use it in a regular hospital

00:10:32.866 --> 00:10:35.000
under the guidance of a regular doctor.

00:10:35.000 --> 00:10:36.866
The next question about

