00:10:38.400 --> 00:10:41.000
using microneedle products

00:10:41.000 --> 00:10:43.266
is whether niacinamide is not suitable for dry skin.

00:10:43.266 --> 00:10:45.900
In fact, there is a famous saying in our chemical field

00:10:45.900 --> 00:10:49.466
that it is nonsense to talk about efficacy without considering the dosage.

00:10:49.666 --> 00:10:52.500
So high-content single niacinamide

00:10:52.500 --> 00:10:55.266
may not be suitable for dry skin because of oil control.

00:10:55.300 --> 00:10:57.233
But if you have a suitable content

00:10:57.233 --> 00:10:59.733
and match it with a sufficiently moisturizing system

00:10:59.733 --> 00:11:01.633
to make a finished product,

00:11:01.633 --> 00:11:03.900
dry skin can still use niacinamide.

00:11:04.000 --> 00:11:06.100
Then why did I not recommend it for dry skin

00:11:06.100 --> 00:11:07.333
when talking about niacinamide

00:11:07.333 --> 00:11:09.300
in the 16-type whitening method

00:11:09.300 --> 00:11:11.333
? Because when used for whitening,

00:11:11.333 --> 00:11:14.266
the recommended dosage of niacinamide is about 5%

00:11:14.266 --> 00:11:15.533
or more. This dosage

00:11:15.533 --> 00:11:17.300
has a certain oil control effect

00:11:17.300 --> 00:11:18.866
on dry skin,

00:11:19.000 --> 00:11:21.233
but it does not mean that dry

00:11:21.233 --> 00:11:22.033
skin

00:11:22.033 --> 00:11:25.700
Niacinamide cannot be used on dry skin because, for example, a repair lotion or cream

00:11:25.700 --> 00:11:26.633
made with 3% to 4% niacinamide

00:11:26.700 --> 00:11:29.866
is also very effective in repairing dry skin.

00:11:29.933 --> 00:11:31.066
In a nutshell,

00:11:31.066 --> 00:11:32.833
niacinamide can be used on dry skin

00:11:32.833 --> 00:11:35.833
, but it is generally used for repairing dry skin

00:11:35.833 --> 00:11:37.266
rather than whitening.

00:11:37.600 --> 00:11:38.533
The next question is,

00:11:38.533 --> 00:11:39.733
a friend said that

00:11:39.733 --> 00:11:42.066
when he took a selfie with his mobile phone,

00:11:42.066 --> 00:11:44.400
he felt that his skin had large pores

00:11:44.400 --> 00:11:46.866
and many red and black spots,

00:11:46.866 --> 00:11:48.200
which looked very rough.

00:11:48.200 --> 00:11:49.233
He asked me what to do.

00:11:49.400 --> 00:11:52.200
This is actually not a skin color problem

00:11:52.200 --> 00:11:53.500
, but another area

00:11:53.500 --> 00:11:55.666
related to pores.

00:11:55.666 --> 00:11:57.833
Since I can't see the photo of your skin

00:11:57.833 --> 00:11:59.000
, I can only guess

00:11:59.000 --> 00:12:01.400
that these red and black spots

00:12:01.400 --> 00:12:04.033
may be... A mixture of glycated pores

00:12:04.033 --> 00:12:06.800
and inflammatory pores.

00:12:06.866 --> 00:12:07.633
Simply put

00:12:07.633 --> 00:12:11.033
, the inflammation and glycation inside our skin

00:12:11.033 --> 00:12:12.666
are reflected in the pores,

00:12:12.666 --> 00:12:14.466
which means the pores become darker

00:12:14.466 --> 00:12:17.800
and deeper. If you want to determine which type it is,

00:12:17.800 --> 00:12:20.733
you can zoom in on the skin photo

00:12:20.733 --> 00:12:23.400
and look closely at the shape of the pores.

00:12:23.400 --> 00:12:24.600
If the

00:12:24.600 --> 00:12:26.300
edges of the pores are a little black

00:12:26.300 --> 00:12:27.400
and there

00:12:27.400 --> 00:12:28.433
seem to

00:12:28.433 --> 00:12:30.833
be some red bumps underneath, then

00:12:30.833 --> 00:12:32.666
it is an inflammatory pore.

00:12:32.866 --> 00:12:34.500
If the pores

00:12:34.500 --> 00:12:36.400
are not red underneath

00:12:36.400 --> 00:12:38.700
but the edges are brown, then

00:12:38.700 --> 00:12:40.466
it is a glycated pore.

00:12:40.500 --> 00:12:43.633
The more common pore treatment methods on the market

00:12:43.633 --> 00:12:45.633
are generally to use mud masks to clean

00:12:45.633 --> 00:12:47.266
or acid. To peel

00:12:47.266 --> 00:12:49.533
or use A-alcohol to shrink pores

00:12:49.600 --> 00:12:50.333
, but in fact,

00:12:50.333 --> 00:12:52.800
our pores are divided into 5 types

00:12:52.800 --> 00:12:56.000
, and different types have different solutions.

00:12:56.033 --> 00:12:57.666
As for this friend's problem,

00:12:57.666 --> 00:13:00.000
if he has inflammatory pores,

00:13:00.000 --> 00:13:03.333
I suggest that he use soothing and anti-inflammatory products

00:13:03.333 --> 00:13:07.400
to soothe and anti-inflammatory the entire face.

00:13:07.533 --> 00:13:09.833
When his inflammation slowly subsides and

00:13:09.833 --> 00:13:11.700
the skin is soothed enough,

00:13:11.700 --> 00:13:13.833
the red and black spots

00:13:13.833 --> 00:13:14.866
will also disappear.

00:13:14.933 --> 00:13:18.133
How to choose soothing and anti-inflammatory products?

00:13:18.133 --> 00:13:20.200
In fact, it is a more complicated issue.

00:13:20.200 --> 00:13:22.666
It depends on your skin type.

00:13:22.733 --> 00:13:24.633
For example, if you have oily skin

00:13:24.633 --> 00:13:25.533
and want to fight inflammation,

00:13:25.533 --> 00:13:26.800
you can use witch hazel

00:13:26.800 --> 00:13:28.400
, calendula, or olive.

00:13:28.400 --> 00:13:29.833
But if you have dry skin,

00:13:29.833 --> 00:13:33.033
you need to use ceramide or B5 for anti-inflammatory.

00:13:33.133 --> 00:13:33.933
This problem

00:13:33.933 --> 00:13:35.633
is very complicated

00:13:35.633 --> 00:13:37.800
and there are many types of pores

00:13:37.800 --> 00:13:39.700
. So if you are interested,

00:13:39.700 --> 00:13:42.600
we can talk about the pore problem later

